<h1> Dashboard </h1>
<div style="width:90%; position: relative; left:5%;">
<text> 
The dashboard visualizes the complexity of your top ten tracks, using danceability, energy, speechiness, acousticness, liveness.
The bar charts show the total complexity score of a track by combining the different track statistics to show the overall complexity of a track.
If you scroll over an individual bar chart the pie chart changes to only show the track statistics for that track.
Next the pie chart combines all of your top ten tracks to show a break down of the five different track statistics through all your top ten tracks.
If you scroll over a track statistic in the pie chart the bar charts change to only show that track, allowing you to compare your top ten tracks
</text>
</div>
<h1> Track Analysis </h1>
<div style="width:90%; position: relative; left:5%;">
<text>
The Track Analysis section allows you to visualize information about your top ten tracks. By hovering over the image you reveal the statistics
for that song, showing Danceability, Energy, Loudness, Speechiness, Acousticness, Instrumentalness, Liveness, and Valence for that track. Mode, Key, and Tempo
are always displayed for each song. You can also click the "Show All" button to open all the statistics for every track in your top ten, allowing you to easily compare them.
Hitting "Close All" will close all the statistics once they are opened.
</text>
</div>
<h1> Sunburst Analysis </h1>
<div style="width:90%; position: relative; left:5%; padding-bottom: 20px;">
<text>
The Sunburst section analyzes data in your top 50 tracks. It uses them to create a tree, made out of artists, albums, and songs. All the artists with tracks in your top 50 are in the innermost layer
of the sunburst. If you click on an artist the sunburst will zoom in, giving you more information about that particular artist. In the second layer, it is broken down to the albums from those artists that have tracks on them that are in your top 50. 
Clicking on an album will zoom it in further, allowing you to see exactly which songs from that album are in your top 50. On the outermost level, the leaves of the tree, you find 
the tracks that are present in your top 50. Hovering over any part of the sunburst will provide a tooltip with information about that section of the graph.
</text>
</div>
